## 1. Introduction

### 1.1 Purpose

This TDD specifies HOW to implement the Zero-Training UX improvements for KB Web Viewer. It covers: file structure, module design, API implementation, client-side architecture, and deployment approach.

### 1.2 Scope

* 7 new JavaScript modules (one per feature)
* 1 new CSS file (design tokens + shared styles)
* 3 new Python API route handlers
* Modifications to 5 existing HTML generator files
* No database schema changes

### 1.3 Technology Stack

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Layer | Technology | Version |
| Language (Server) | Python | 3.11+ |
| Language (Client) | JavaScript (ES6 modules) | ES2020 |
| Styling | CSS Custom Properties | CSS3 |
| Server | Python http.server (stdlib) | Built-in |
| Storage (Client) | localStorage | Web API |
| Build Tool | None | N/A (no build step) |

### 1.4 Design Principles

* **Progressive Enhancement** — UX features enhance but never break existing functionality
* **Separation of Concerns** — each feature is an independent module
* **Data-Driven** — content (tooltips, tour steps) in JSON config, not hardcoded
* **Graceful Degradation** — features fail silently if dependencies unavailable
* **200-line limit** — every file stays under 200 lines

### 1.5 Constraints

* No npm packages or CDN dependencies
* No build tools (webpack, rollup, etc.)
* All JS loaded as ES6 modules via <script type="module">
* Must work in Chrome/Firefox/Edge (last 2 versions)
* Dark theme only (no theme switching)
* Python server uses string templates (no Jinja2)

