## 2. System Architecture

### 2.1 Architecture Overview

The UX enhancement layer sits between the existing HTML pages and the user. It’s loaded as ES6 modules that initialize after DOM ready. Each module is self-contained and communicates via a lightweight event bus.

┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ Browser │
│ │
│ ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐│
│ │ Existing HTML Pages (server-rendered) ││
│ │ viewer\_html.py → Graph page (4 tabs) ││
│ │ viewer\_dashboard\_html.py → Dashboard ││
│ │ viewer\_tags\_html.py → Tags ││
│ │ viewer\_quality\_html.py → Quality ││
│ │ viewer\_analytics\_html.py → Analytics ││
│ └──────────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────┘│
│ │ DOM ready │
│ ┌──────────────────────────▼───────────────────────────────┐│
│ │ UX Enhancement Layer (ES6 Modules) ││
│ │ ││
│ │ ┌─────────┐ ┌──────────┐ ┌────────────┐ ┌────────────┐ ││
│ │ │ tour.js │ │tooltips.js│ │empty-states│ │recommendations││
│ │ └────┬────┘ └─────┬────┘ └─────┬──────┘ └──────┬─────┘ ││
│ │ │ │ │ │ ││
│ │ ┌────▼────┐ ┌─────▼────┐ ┌────▼─────┐ ┌──────▼──────┐ ││
│ │ │graph- │ │help-panel│ │ui-tokens │ │ event-bus │ ││
│ │ │analysis │ │ │ │ (.css) │ │ │ ││
│ │ └─────────┘ └──────────┘ └──────────┘ └─────────────┘ ││
│ └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘│
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

### 2.2 Component Diagram

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Component | Responsibility | Technology |
| tour.js | Onboarding tour overlay, step navigation | Vanilla JS, CSS animations |
| tooltips.js | ? icon injection, tooltip popup management | Vanilla JS, CSS positioning |
| empty-states.js | Detect empty sections, render empty state UI | Vanilla JS, DOM manipulation |
| recommendations.js | Fetch/display recommendations, handle Fix Now | Vanilla JS, fetch API |
| graph-analysis.js | Client-side graph algorithms, insights panel | Vanilla JS, BFS/DFS |
| help-panel.js | Slide-in panel, markdown rendering, content loading | Vanilla JS, fetch API |
| event-bus.js | Cross-module communication | Custom Events API |
| ui-tokens.css | Design tokens, shared component styles | CSS Custom Properties |

