## 10. Deployment Considerations

### 10.1 File Deployment

All new files go into shared/viewer/ directory which is already served by the Python HTTP server’s \_serve\_static() function. No server restart required for JS/CSS changes.

### 10.2 Python Module Deployment

New Python files (ux\_routes.py, recommendation\_engine.py, graph\_analyzer.py) require server restart. They integrate via the existing route handler pattern in viewer\_server.py.

### 10.3 Rollback Strategy

1. **JS/CSS rollback**: Delete files from shared/viewer/modules/ and shared/viewer/config/ — pages revert to no-UX-enhancement state
2. **Python rollback**: Remove import of ux\_routes from viewer\_server.py — new API endpoints become 404
3. **Full rollback**: Revert the HTML template changes in viewer\_\*\_html.py files — removes all <script type="module"> tags

### 10.4 Feature Flags

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Flag | Default | Description |
| localStorage: kb-viewer-ux-disabled | false | Master kill switch for all UX enhancements |
| Config: tour.enabled | true | Enable/disable onboarding tour |
| Config: tooltips.enabled | true | Enable/disable tooltips |
| Config: analysis.enabled | true | Enable/disable graph auto-analysis |

