### Phase 9: HTML Migration — Shared Viewer Pages (KSA-93 addendum)

**Problem:** All 3 MCP modules (Python, Node.js, Kotlin) embed identical HTML/CSS/JS as string constants in server code. This violates DRY — any UI change requires updating 15+ files across 3 languages.

**Solution:** Migrate 4 sub-pages to shared/viewer/\*.html files (single source of truth). All 3 servers serve from disk instead of constants.

**Files to create:** - [ ] shared/viewer/dashboard.html — extracted from Python viewer\_dashboard\_html.py - [ ] shared/viewer/tags.html — extracted from Python viewer\_tags\_html.py - [ ] shared/viewer/quality.html — extracted from Python viewer\_quality\_html.py - [ ] shared/viewer/analytics.html — extracted from Python viewer\_analytics\_html.py

**Server updates (serve from disk with fallback):** - [ ] Python viewer\_server.py — replace \_serve\_page(handler, CONSTANT) with \_load\_shared\_page(handler, "page.html") - [ ] Kotlin ViewerServer.kt — replace call.respondText(CONSTANT) with call.respondText(loadSharedPage("page.html")) - [ ] Node.js viewer-server.ts — replace this.servePage(res, CONSTANT) with this.serveSharedPage(res, "page.html")

**Files to delete (~15 files):** - [ ] Python: viewer\_dashboard\_html.py, viewer\_tags\_html.py, viewer\_quality\_html.py, viewer\_analytics\_html.py - [ ] Node.js: viewer-dashboard-html.ts, viewer-tags-html.ts, viewer-quality-html.ts, viewer-analytics-html.ts, viewer-html.ts - [ ] Kotlin: ViewerDashboardHtml.kt, ViewerTagsHtml.kt, ViewerQualityHtml.kt, ViewerAnalyticsHtml.kt, ViewerHtml.kt

**Fallback logic:** If shared HTML file not found on disk → serve minimal error page (not crash). This handles case where shared/viewer/ is missing (e.g., running server standalone without workspace).

**Architecture after migration:**

shared/viewer/
├── index.html (graph page — already migrated)
├── dashboard.html (NEW — from embedded constants)
├── tags.html (NEW — from embedded constants)
├── quality.html (NEW — from embedded constants)
├── analytics.html (NEW — from embedded constants)
├── ui-tokens.css
├── ux-components.css
├── modules/ (UX enhancement modules)
└── config/ (tour/tooltip configs)

3 servers → all serve from shared/viewer/\*.html (single source of truth)

## 12. Appendix

### Glossary

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Term | Definition |
| ES6 Module | JavaScript module loaded via <script type="module"> |
| Design Token | CSS custom property defining a design value |
| Spotlight | Tour pattern: dim page, illuminate target element |
| Event Bus | Pub/sub pattern for decoupled module communication |
| Progressive Enhancement | Features add value but page works without them |

### Open Questions

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| # | Question | Status | Answer |
| 1 | Should graph analysis run server-side or client-side? | Resolved | Hybrid: server provides data, client runs algorithms for <500 nodes, server for larger graphs |
| 2 | How to handle shared/viewer/ not existing? | Resolved | Python server falls back to inline HTML constants (existing behavior) |
| 3 | Should help content be static JSON or dynamic from USER-GUIDE.md? | Resolved | Static JSON extracted from USER-GUIDE.md at build time (manual process) |